Subject: [PATCH] SPV: skip DebugGlobalVariable Variable operand for composite constants

The NonSemantic.Shader.DebugInfo.100 spec restricts the Variable operand
of DebugGlobalVariable to one of:
- OpVariable result-id,
- OpConstant result-id (scalar), or
- DebugInfoNone result-id.

Builder::createConstVariable currently passes the constant id straight
through. For scalar OpConstant initialisers that is fine, but for
composite or spec-constant-composite initialisers (including the
implicit gl_WorkGroupSize synthesised from
`layout(local_size_x = ...) in;` in every compute shader, and any
file-scope `const vec3 foo[] = vec3[](...)` array) the result-id refers
to OpConstantComposite / OpSpecConstantComposite, which the spec does
not allow. spirv-val rejects those modules with
VUID-VkShaderModuleCreateInfo-pCode-08737, breaking
vkCreateShaderModule whenever the validation layer is loaded.

Substitute DebugInfoNone for those cases so spirv-val accepts the
module while still emitting a DebugGlobalVariable that carries the
symbol's Name, Type, Source and Line for SPIR-V debug-info consumers.

This is a downstream-local patch carried via CPM PATCHES while we wait
for the upstream fix; see related KhronosGroup/glslang #4186 (which
covers the analogous DebugTypeArray Component-Count case).
---
diff --git a/SPIRV/SpvBuilder.cpp b/SPIRV/SpvBuilder.cpp
--- a/SPIRV/SpvBuilder.cpp
+++ b/SPIRV/SpvBuilder.cpp
@@ -2874,7 +2874,15 @@ void Builder::createConstVariable(Id type, const char* name, Id constant, bool i
     if (emitNonSemanticShaderDebugInfo) {
         Id debugType = getDebugType(type);
         if (isGlobal) {
-            createDebugGlobalVariable(debugType, name, constant);
+            // NonSemantic.Shader.DebugInfo.100 restricts the Variable
+            // operand of DebugGlobalVariable to OpVariable, OpConstant
+            // (scalar) or DebugInfoNone. Composite / spec-constant
+            // initialisers (incl. synthesised gl_WorkGroupSize) hit
+            // OpConstantComposite / OpSpecConstantComposite which are
+            // not in the allowed set; pass DebugInfoNone instead so
+            // spirv-val accepts the module.
+            const Id variableOperand = (getOpCode(constant) == Op::OpConstant) ? constant : makeDebugInfoNone();
+            createDebugGlobalVariable(debugType, name, variableOperand);
         }
         else {
             auto debugLocal = createDebugLocalVariable(debugType, name);
